Former UEFA boss Michel Platini was placed in police custody on Tuesday as part of the French investigation into corruption over the conditions for the awarding of the 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar. learned from close source of the investigation, confirming a Mediapart information. The former Secretary General of the Elysee under the presidency of Nicolas Sarkozy, Claude Gueant, for his part is heard in open hearing by the investigators of the anti-corruption office of the judicial police (OCLCIFF) in Nanterre, near Paris , according to this source. - AFP 